         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">27/5/84 ¶  ¶ By a strange oversight, dear Sir Joseph, I missed to recollect, that the 5th vol. of DC.'s monographiae contains a complete elaboration of the known Cyrtandreae. ¶  The volume came during...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.05.27</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Archives, Miscellaneous correspondence.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found in 1998 with the specimen K831965 in the Kew Herbarium.</p>
               </note>27/5/84</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>By a strange oversight, dear Sir Joseph, I missed to recollect, that the 5th vol. of DC.'s monographiae contains a complete elaboration of the known Cyrtandreae.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">C. B. Clarke (1883).</p>
               </note> The volume came during my illness, and I found out my shortcoming only after I sent off the msc. of a supposed n.g. (<name key="Chalmersia">Chalmersia</name>) by last mail.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Hooker, 19 May 1884 (in this edition as 84-05-19a). M never erected a genus <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Chalmersia">Chalmersia</name>
                     </seg>; he described <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Dichrotrichum%20">Dichrotrichum </name>chalmersii</seg> in B84.06.02, p. 14. However, S. Moore (1899), p. 174 quoted <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Chalmersia">Chalmersia</name> papuana</seg> from 'Baron von Mueller's type at Kew'.</p>
               </note> Now I see, that it is a new species of Dichrotrichum, which as I indicated before should be named in honor of the Rev. James Chalmers, who brought it from the higher regions of Mt Stanley Range, New Guinea.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I did not recognize the genus in the "genera"<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83), vol. 2, part 2, p. 1014. See also M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 30 May 1884.</p>
               </note> as Mr Bentham attributed unconditionally "folia opposita" to it.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Chalmersia">Chalmersia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cyrtandreae%20">Cyrtandreae </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dichrotrichum%20">Dichrotrichum </name>
            </p>
